KwaZulu-Natal police have called on the community to help them identify the body which was found by herdsmen in Ntendeka area in Madadeni outside New Castle. According to the police, a badly mutilated body of a white man, who is believed to be in his forties was discovered by herdsmen who were tending to their livestock on Monday. Police spokesperson Thembeka Mbele said the deceased had tattoos drawn on his body. “The deceased had a flower on his right shoulder and on his left arm,” Mbele said. Anyone with information can contact  Captain Lawrence Khumalo on 082 469 9425 or Warrant Officer Ntokozo Mbatha on 063 091 3419, or alternatively call Crime Stop on 08600 10111. -AfroVoice Reporter